.Sh CAVEATS
Nonce reuse breaks both confidentiality and authenticity.
Every key and nonce pair must be unique.
The 192-bit nonce makes random nonce generation safe for this purpose.
.Pp
The key must be uniformly random. When using a password, a suitable
password-based key derivation function must be used to derive it.
.Pp
Cannot be used for large file or stream encryption in a single call: a
cryptographic chunked encryption protocol must be used to split streams into
sealed packets.
.Pp
.Sh BUGS
There is no way to distinguish authentication failures from the backend
failures when opening ciphertexts. This is deliberate. Normally, after the
context is successfully allocated, no other failures are expected from the
backend.
